item.title: Crown cuts dividend as profits plunge
item.description: Crown Resorts has ditched its final dividend payout to shareholders.

item.title: Breakthrough in body mystery
item.description: Queensland police have launched a fresh public appeal for information to help identify a man whose body was found in a dam near Nambour 12 years ago.

item.title: Victoria on a virus ‘downslope’
item.description: The chief medical officer says Victoria is on a “downslope” of coronavirus cases as the state recorded 216 new infections overnight, the lowest daily figure in a month.

item.title: Chadstone mall owner’s eye-watering loss
item.description: Shopping mall owners Vicinity Centres has reported a massive financial haemorrhage as the economic downturn caused by COVID-19 has drastically reduced the value of its commercial property portfolio.

item.title: Tornado causes destruction in city’s south
item.description: An Adelaide suburb has experienced a low-grade tornado overnight, which ripped through a street and tore down trees and powers lines.

item.title: 7 new COVID cases in NSW
item.description: There have been 7 new cases of coronavirus diagnosed in NSW up to 8pm on Tuesday night.

item.title: Major medical company’s vaccine deal
item.description: Biotechnology giant CSL says it has secured a partnership to develop a potential vaccine to fight against the coronavirus.

item.title: Taupau reveals ‘scary’ concussion ordeal
item.description: Manly prop Martin Taupau battled memory loss and suffered headaches for days after being knocked out for the first time in his career against the New Zealand Warriors a fortnight ago.

item.title: Virus vaccine should be ‘mandatory’: PM
item.description: A coronavirus vaccine should be as “mandatory as possible” for Australians, Prime Minister Scott Morrison says.

item.title: Free preschool for term 4
item.description: Preschool education across New South Wales will remain a free service until the end of this year.
